text.tspan: Remittance costs as a proportion of the amount remitted, 2011 to 2019
Remittance costs as a proportion of the amount of money remitted. Remittances are financial transfers from
non-residents to residents of a country, such as a worker abroad sending money to family and friends, or from
short-term, seasonal work in another country.
